#: ../../A/astroturfing.rst:5
msgid "astroturfing"
msgstr "astroturfing"

#: ../../A/astroturfing.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../A/astroturfing.rst:10
msgid ""
"The use of paid shills to create the impression of a popular movement, "
"through means like letters to newspapers from soi-disant ‘concerned "
"citizens’, paid opinion pieces, and the formation of grass-roots lobbying "
"groups that are actually funded by a PR group (AstroTurf is fake grass; "
"hence the term). See also :ref:`sock-puppet`\\, :ref:`tentacle`\\."
msgstr ""
"金で雇ったサクラを使って、草の根運動が起きているかのような印象を作り出すこと。たとえば自称‘憂慮する市民’からの新聞への投書、金で書かせた論説、実際にはPR会社が資金を出している草の根ロビー団体の結成といった手段による(AstroTurfは人工芝。そこからこの用語が来ている)。\\"
" :ref:`sock-puppet`\\ 、\\ :ref:`tentacle`\\ も参照。"

#: ../../A/astroturfing.rst:14
msgid ""
"What an individual posting to a public forum under an assumed name is said "
"to be doing."
msgstr "個人が偽名で公開フォーラムに投稿することを指してこう言う。"

#: ../../A/astroturfing.rst:16
msgid ""
"This term became common among hackers after it came to light in early 1998 "
"that Microsoft had attempted to use such tactics to forestall the U.S. "
"Department of Justice's antitrust action against the company. The maneuver "
"backfired horribly, angering a number of state attorneys-general enough to "
"induce them to go public with plans to join the Federal suit. It also set "
"anybody defending Microsoft on the net for the accusation \"You're just "
"astroturfing! \"."
msgstr ""
"この用語は、1998年初頭にMicrosoftが、米国司法省の同社に対する独占禁止法訴訟を未然に防ぐためこうした戦術を使おうとしていたことが明るみに出た後、ハッカーの間で一般的になった。この策略はひどく裏目に出て、何人かの州司法長官を、連邦訴訟に加わる計画を公表するに足るほど怒らせた。また、ネット上でMicrosoftを擁護する者は誰でも「お前はastroturfingしているだけだ!」という非難を浴びることになった。"
